    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, remove the pan from heat and add the <strong>drained orecchiette</strong>, <strong>chopped wilted spinach</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up until the cheese has melted and the pasta is coated in the sauce – this is your<strong> goats' cheese & sun-dried tomato sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
